0,000 mark for the first time ever, proving naysayers wrong. I do not own Bitcoin, but I have exposure to cryptocurrencies through my investment in Coinbase Global Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/COIN\" title=\"Coinbase Global, Inc.\">COIN</a>). Bitcoin</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2138995594/image_2138995594.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742818-bitcoin-empirical-evidence-and-fundamentals-call-for-higher-prices", "pub_date": "2024-12-07 18:14:13"}, {"id": "4742223", "title": "Powell Industries: Don't Chase This Rally - No Margin Of Safety", "description": "<figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/184983574/image_184983574.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Thumbs Down (XXXL)\" data-id=\"184983574\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1205px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/184983574/image_184983574.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/184983574/image_184983574.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/184983574/image_184983574.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/184983574/image_184983574.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/184983574/image_184983574.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/184983574/image_184983574.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/184983574/image_184983574.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/184983574/image_184983574.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">4FR</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2> </h2> <h2>Powell Industries: Don't Chase This Rally - Baked In Upside Triggers Downgrade</h2> <p><span>We previously covered </span><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4718509-powell-industries-has-rarely-been-cheaper-upgrade-buy\" title=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4718509-powell-industries-has-rarely-been-cheaper-upgrade-buy\" target=\"_blank\">Powell Industries, Inc.</a><span> (NASDAQ:</span><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/POWL\" title=\"Powell Industries, Inc.\">POWL</a></span><span>) in September 2024, discussing its bright prospects attributed to </span><span>the higher oil/gas/ petroleum industry-wide capex and increased electrical power</span></p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/184983574/image_184983574.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742223-powell-industries-dont-chase-this-rally-no-margin-of-safety", "pub_date": "2024-12-07 18:00:00"}, {"id": "4742816", "title": "Jobs Prints As Expected, But Geopolitical Risk Escalates; Inflation Lingers", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/511515604/image_511515604.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"The dominance of the Russian Federation in geopolitics. Concept\" data-id=\"511515604\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"828px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/511515604/image_511515604.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/511515604/image_511515604.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/511515604/image_511515604.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/511515604/image_511515604.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/511515604/image_511515604.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/511515604/image_511515604.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/511515604/image_511515604.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/511515604/image_511515604.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">Waldemarus/iStock via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p><strong>NEW YORK (Dec. 6th)</strong> - The Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS) announced 227,000 new jobs for November this morning, according to the Establishment Survey, a collection of job creation data from businesses replying to the survey. The number is slightly above the</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/511515604/image_511515604.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742816-jobs-prints-as-expected-geopolitical-risk-escalates-inflation-lingers", "pub_date": "2024-12-07 17:48:49"}, {"id": "4742815", "title": "Buy 3 December Barron's Better Bet 'Safer' Dividend Dogs Of 23", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1269694356/image_1269694356.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Group of three dogs celebrating christmas with a santa claus and reindeer antlers hat with a red ribbon. Isolated on gray background.\" data-id=\"1269694356\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"527px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1269694356/image_1269694356.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1269694356/image_1269694356.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1269694356/image_1269694356.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1269694356/image_1269694356.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1269694356/image_1269694356.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1269694356/image_1269694356.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1269694356/image_1269694356.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1269694356/image_1269694356.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">smrm1977/iStock via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2><strong>Foreword</strong></h2> <p>While half of this collection of <a href=\"https://www.barrons.com/articles/dividend-stocks-yield-treasuries-bonds-ef790bd7?mod=Searchresults\" rel=\"nofollow\">Barron\u2019s Better Bets</a> (BBB) is too pricey, or reveals somewhat skinny dividends, six of the ten lowest priced Dogs of the BBB are ready to buy along with three more outside</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1269694356/image_1269694356.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742815-buy-3-december-barrons-better-bet-safer-dividend-dogs-of-23", "pub_date": "2024-12-07 17:40:34"}, {"id": "4742795", "title": "GigaCloud Is Discounted For Good Reasons - Reiterate Hold", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/174636177/image_174636177.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Budget Cuts\" data-id=\"174636177\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1028px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/174636177/image_174636177.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/174636177/image_174636177.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/174636177/image_174636177.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/174636177/image_174636177.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/174636177/image_174636177.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/174636177/image_174636177.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/174636177/image_174636177.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/174636177/image_174636177.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"></p> <p class=\"item-credits\">TimAbramowitz</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>GigaCloud Is Discounted For Good Reasons - Reiterate Hold</h2> <p>We previously covered <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4717918-gigacloud-bullish-support-missing-high-growth-goes-unrewarded-for-now-downgrade\">GigaCloud Technology Inc.</a> (NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GCT#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link\">GCT</a>) in August 2024, discussing its significant volatility after <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4109302-gigacloud-technology-sinks-after-grizzly-research-short-report\">the short attacks</a>, along with the <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4128115-traders-pause-for-breath-after-wall-street-wipeout-whats-next\">market rotation from high</a></p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/174636177/image_174636177.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742795-gigacloud-is-discounted-for-good-reasons-reiterate-hold", "pub_date": "2024-12-07 17:30:00"}, {"id": "4742709", "title": "Who Said ~ 9% Yields Cannot Grow Further? Consider These 2 Picks", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1398472101/image_1398472101.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Pink piggy banks on ascending stacks of paper currency\" data-id=\"1398472101\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1008px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1398472101/image_1398472101.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1398472101/image_1398472101.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1398472101/image_1398472101.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1398472101/image_1398472101.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1398472101/image_1398472101.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1398472101/image_1398472101.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1398472101/image_1398472101.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1398472101/image_1398472101.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">PM Images</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>When I see securities producing extremely attractive yields, the immediate thing what comes to my mind is that most likely it is some form of a value trap. Namely, abnormal yields usually are there because of how the market has</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1398472101/image_1398472101.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742709-who-said-9-percent-yields-cannot-grow-further-consider-these-2-picks", "pub_date": "2024-12-07 17:15:00"}, {"id": "4742785", "title": "DocuSign: Time To Start Taking Profits Here (Rating Downgrade)", "description": "<figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1162476186/image_1162476186.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"DocuSign headquarters building\" data-id=\"1162476186\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"6000px\" height=\"4000px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1162476186/image_1162476186.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1162476186/image_1162476186.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1162476186/image_1162476186.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1162476186/image_1162476186.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1162476186/image_1162476186.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1162476186/image_1162476186.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1162476186/image_1162476186.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1162476186/image_1162476186.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">Michael Vi</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>As we head into the end of the year, we find that the Q3 earnings season (now with a flurry of results for companies that feature a January year-end) continues to be a major upside driver for rebound stocks, with investors cheering companies that</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1162476186/image_1162476186.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742785-docusign-time-to-start-taking-profits-here-rating-downgrade", "pub_date": "2024-12-07 17:00:37"}, {"id": "4742814", "title": "Sector Spotlight: Industrial REITs - Still A Real Estate Darling?", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1331173454/image_1331173454.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Wide shot of worker opening loading door in warehouse\" data-id=\"1331173454\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1025px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1331173454/image_1331173454.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1331173454/image_1331173454.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1331173454/image_1331173454.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1331173454/image_1331173454.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1331173454/image_1331173454.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1331173454/image_1331173454.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1331173454/image_1331173454.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1331173454/image_1331173454.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">Thomas Barwick</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div></p> <p>It\u2019s called the business cycle because things are always changing.</p> <p>In February of 2020, COVID brought world economies to their knees with an effective cessation of life as we knew it. Non-essential offices and workplaces shut down. Stores, restaurants, and entertainment venues closed as personal contact became untenable. E-commerce surged and to combat supply chain bottlenecks, retailers and manufacturers leased more warehouse space. The COVID era\u2019s low-interest rate environment enabled developers to meet new industrial demand by ramping up new warehouse construction.</p> <p>4 \u00bd years later, we are coming off an unprecedentedly steep, inflation-fighting series of hikes to the Fed Funds rate. New construction has slowed to a trickle and demand may be waning. A few weeks back, Home Depot (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HD\" title=\"The Home Depot, Inc.\">HD</a>) <a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/home-depot-is-dropping-warehouses-in-a-shifting-retail-market-4f8e581a?st=XinZMR&amp;reflink=desktopwebshare_permalink\" rel=\"nofollow\">announced</a> its intention to sublease almost 4.7 million square feet of warehouse space it leased during the pandemic. A Savills <a href=\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/party-over-industrial-vacancy-hits-211330357.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">report</a>, summarized by Yahoo Finance and The Real Deal, describes that industrial vacancy has hit a 10-year high, exacerbated by the growing amount of sublease space available.</p> <p>In recent years, industrial/logistics real estate had arguably become the most desirable property type. Lately, not so much. In this Sector Spotlight we will examine, in the realm of industrial REIT investment, where we have been, where we are now, and where we might be headed. We compare market valuations relative to AFFO/share, Net Asset Value (NAV), and 3Q24 Same-Store Net Operating Income (SSNOI).</p> <p><strong>2024 Returns</strong></p> <p>3Q 2024 Industrial REIT earnings reports were largely positive with sustained strong occupancy and re-leasing roll-ups. Investors, however, seemed unimpressed and share price performance ranged from slightly negative to blood-in-the-streets.</p> <p><strong>Industrial REITs: 2024 Total Returns through 12/05/2024</strong></p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture> <span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/6/1024916-17335277213868766_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"916\" data-height=\"426\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/6/1024916-17335277213868766.png\" alt=\"A graph of a number of people Description automatically generated with medium confidence\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"><span>S&amp;P Capital IQ</span></p></figcaption></figure></p> <p>Source: S&amp;P Capital IQ as of 12/05/2024</p> <p><strong>Market Valuations</strong></p> <p>Various metrics can be applied to understand a company\u2019s intrinsic value relative to its market valuation. At <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/mp/1336-portfolio-income-solutions/articles\">Portfolio Income Solutions</a> we put significant trust in Adjusted Funds from Operations (AFFO/share) measures because they level the earnings playing field in a peer set. At present, the AFFO/share multiples of the Industrial REIT sector look like this.</p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture> <span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/6/1024916-1733527721428305_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"800\" data-height=\"433\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/6/1024916-1733527721428305.png\" alt=\"A screenshot of a computer Description automatically generated\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"><span>2MCAC with data derived from S&amp;P Capital IQ</span></p></figcaption></figure></p> <p>An average P/AFFO multiple of 20.2x prices the sector north of the whole REIT universe multiple of 17.5x, but the valuation variance within the set is extreme. Plymouth Industrial (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PLYM\" title=\"Plymouth Industrial REIT, Inc.\">PLYM</a>) is trading at an AFFO multiple of approximately 1/3 that of Terreno Realty (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TRNO\" title=\"Terreno Realty Corporation\">TRNO</a>). The market losses in the graph above are a reflection of how dramatically investor attitudes have changed in recent history and how that translates to trading multiples.</p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture> <span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/6/1024916-17335277214461462_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"696\" data-height=\"382\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/6/1024916-17335277214461462.png\" alt=\"A graph of a number of bars Description automatically generated with medium confidence\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"><span>2MCAC with data derived from S&amp;P Capital IQ</span></p></figcaption></figure></p> <p>Source: 2MCAC</p> <p>With the sector AFFO multiple falling from 35.5x in 2021 to a recent 20.5x, you can ascertain that investor enthusiasm for investment in industrial real estate has waned significantly. In an era of protracted Magnificent 7 outperformance, identification of industrial REITs as a prime source for tax-loss harvesting might also contribute to recent price declines.</p> <p><strong>Same-Store Net Operating Income </strong></p> <p>Third quarter reporting indicated that while the industrial and multifamily sectors are still seeing strong demand, waves of competing new supply have suppressed both rent growth and occupancy. The result is a trend of more tepid SSNOI growth for those sectors. On average, the industrial REIT sector saw same store cash NOI grow 5.9% compared to 3Q23. That\u2019s strong income growth but pales next to the double-digit growth investors paid 35x AFFO just a couple of years prior. The future is unknown, but if growth slows further share prices might continue to fall.</p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/6/1024916-17335277211695216.png\" alt=\"A screenshot of a document Description automatically generated\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"><span>2MCAC with data compiled from S&amp;P Capital IQ</span></p></figcaption></figure></p> <p><strong>Net Asset Value</strong></p> <p>NAV is broadly considered a useful metric for comparison of value relative to market share price and to peers. Twelve months ago, equity REITs traded at a high teens discount to Net Asset Value. Today they trade at close to NAV valuations, but the industrial sector demonstrates extreme variance in market value to estimated intrinsic value. In prior periods the premiere performers like <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PLD\" title=\"Prologis, Inc.\">PLD</a>, <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/REXR\" title=\"Rexford Industrial Realty, Inc.\">REXR</a>, and <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TRNO\" title=\"Terreno Realty Corporation\">TRNO</a> traded at premiums to NAV, but market valuations have come back to earth.</p> <p><figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><picture> <span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/6/1024916-17335277215228817_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"782\" data-height=\"375\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkedin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2024/12/6/1024916-17335277215228817.png\" alt=\"A screenshot of a table Description automatically generated\" contenteditable=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"><span>2MCAC with data compiled from S&amp;P Capital IQ</span></p></figcaption></figure></p> <p>Source: 2MCAC with data compiled from S&amp;P Capital IQ</p> <p>When considering NAVs, it is important to understand that the value is derived from using an assumed capitalization rate. As the table above describes, the applied Cap Rates vary widely. In this case from 4.8% up to 9.0%; the lower the cap rate applied, the higher the NAV derived. Operationally, these companies are extremely diverse, so that is why we see outlying cap rates for the cannabis focused Innovative Industrial Properties (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IIPR\" title=\"Innovative Industrial Properties, Inc.\">IIPR</a>) and the frozen food chain focused Americold Realty Trust (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/COLD\" title=\"Americold Realty Trust, Inc.\">COLD</a>).</p> <p><strong>Takeaways</strong></p> <p>E-commerce and related logistics play an ever-larger role in the US economy, and they have been the driving force in growing the industrial REIT sector. Changing macroeconomic factors have made visible the vulnerability of all types of real estate to supply and demand and made investors painfully aware that trends don\u2019t run on forever.</p> <p>The industrial REIT sector has price corrected significantly (and appropriately) in the last two years. We feel that current pricing makes the sector much more investible and that if shares are being further beaten down by tax-loss selling, then a sustaining strong economy makes them opportunistically priced.</p> <div class=\"before_last_paragraph-piano-placeholder\"></div><p>Happy investing.</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1331173454/image_1331173454.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742814-sector-spotlight-industrial-reits-still-a-real-estate-darling", "pub_date": "2024-12-07 16:44:44"}, {"id": "4741553", "title": "My Single Biggest Regret As A REIT Investor", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1484137360/image_1484137360.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Depressed young man\" data-id=\"1484137360\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\